Fri, Sep 4, 2015, 22:09 BST - UK Markets closed Tim Tebow's chances of making the Eagles just got a huge boost By Emmett Knowlton | Business Insider â€“ 19 minutes ago Print 
(AP Images) 
As NFL preseason draws to a close and teams scramble to make last minute roster cuts, there's notable back-up quarterback news coming out of Philadelphia. 
The NFL Network's Ian Rapoport first reported that the Eagles traded quarterback Matt Barkley to the Arizona Cardinals in exchange for a 7th round pick, meaning that Tim Tebow is in good shape to make Chip Kelly's final 53-man roster. 
The #AZCardinals have traded for #Eagles QB Matt Barkley, source said. @JayGlazer first reported. Further indication Tebow has made the team Tebow falls behind both Sam Bradford and Mark Sanchez on the quarterback depth chart, but may still see a decent amount of playing time in short-yardage situations, and as a two-point specialist. The Eagles open up their regular season on Monday, September 14 against the Falcons.
